-- Create FactWeather table with matching data types (internal sql table)

CREATE TABLE FactWeather (
    clouds_all SMALLINT,
    humidity SMALLINT,
    pressure SMALLINT,
    temp_K FLOAT,
    temp_min_K FLOAT,
    temp_max_K FLOAT,
    feels_like_K FLOAT,
    wind_deg SMALLINT,
    wind_gust FLOAT,
    wind_speed FLOAT,
    rain_1h REAL,
    corrected_timestamp INT,
    location NVARCHAR(100),
    date_time DATETIME2,
    id NVARCHAR(100),
    temp_C FLOAT,
    temp_min_C FLOAT,
    temp_max_C FLOAT,
    feels_like_C FLOAT,
    temp_F FLOAT,
    temp_min_F FLOAT,
    temp_max_F FLOAT,
    feels_like_F FLOAT,
    lat FLOAT,
    lon FLOAT,
    weather_id_value INT,
    weather_main_value NVARCHAR(100),
    weather_description_value NVARCHAR(100),
    weather_icon_value NVARCHAR(100),
    date DATE
);
GO

-- Insert data into FactWeather
--wind columns might be null if you didnt ingest them, so remove them from the insert

INSERT INTO FactWeather (
    clouds_all,
    humidity,
    pressure
)
SELECT 
    clouds_all
    humidity
    pressure
FROM ExternalWeather;
GO
